WEBVTT

1
00:00:59.977 --> 00:01:01.353
'Sup. baby?

2
00:01:18.370 --> 00:01:20.622
Let's do some liquor science.

3
00:01:21.123 --> 00:01:23.542
Um. hey. Rick.

4
00:01:23.750 --> 00:01:25.377
Rick!

5
00:01:25.877 --> 00:01:27.879
Rick! Are you ignoring me?

6
00:01:27.963 --> 00:01:30.591
Hey! Hello! Rick!

7
00:01:31.008 --> 00:01:32.593
Did you go deaf?

8
00:01:33.384 --> 00:01:34.678
No. no. no. no. no!

9
00:01:34.720 --> 00:01:36.722
Oh. my God!

10
00:01:39.558 --> 00:01:40.892
Whoa!

11
00:01:41.643 --> 00:01:43.437
Morty! What the fuck?

12
00:01:43.520 --> 00:01:44.938
I didn't... I didn't mean to!

13
00:01:45.021 --> 00:01:46.857
What the fuck?

14
00:01:47.733 --> 00:01:50.944
Tell me why you ignored a sign
that said "do not disturb."

15
00:01:51.027 --> 00:01:52.613
I... it's not important.

16
00:01:52.696 --> 00:01:55.240
It better be. You just destroyed
my distillery.

17
00:01:55.324 --> 00:01:58.160
So either it's an emergency.
or it's important.

18
00:01:58.243 --> 00:01:59.911
And it better be
real fuckin' important

19
00:01:59.995 --> 00:02:03.457
because this was the most
important thing to me today.

20
00:02:03.540 --> 00:02:07.794
So what did you come down
here for?

21
00:02:08.753 --> 00:02:10.505
I was wondering
if you could drive me

22
00:02:10.589 --> 00:02:13.175
to pick up some Pokemon cards.

23
00:02:14.217 --> 00:02:15.427
I'm sorry.

24
00:02:15.510 --> 00:02:17.346
Have you ever seen
me happy. Morty?

25
00:02:17.429 --> 00:02:20.098
What? Uh. I mean. not really.

26
00:02:20.182 --> 00:02:21.767
Well. I've been happy
in my life.

27
00:02:21.850 --> 00:02:24.227
And. look.
there's no point on the chart

28
00:02:24.269 --> 00:02:26.188
where my joy intersects
with your presence.

29
00:02:26.271 --> 00:02:27.439
Then why hang out with me?

30
00:02:27.481 --> 00:02:29.191
I don't know. When I found you.

31
00:02:29.274 --> 00:02:30.585
you were bait.
When I killed that fish.

32
00:02:30.609 --> 00:02:32.152
maybe I should have cut
the line.

33
00:02:32.235 --> 00:02:34.821
Because all I have now
is a fucking worm.

34
00:02:34.905 --> 00:02:39.034
You told me that wasn't true.
You're just trying to hurt me.

35
00:02:40.369 --> 00:02:42.496
Morty. no. I meant...

36
00:02:42.579 --> 00:02:44.289
Fuck!

37
00:02:44.748 --> 00:02:45.791
God damn it.

38
00:02:45.957 --> 00:02:48.043
This would be the perfect time
for a drink.

39
00:03:20.784 --> 00:03:22.661
Pressure reader.
Fermentation chamber.

40
00:03:22.703 --> 00:03:25.163
Copper lining. Wow.
Morty blew all this up?

41
00:03:25.247 --> 00:03:26.623
What's a mash tun?

42
00:03:26.665 --> 00:03:28.059
Just get an empty beer keg
for that.

43
00:03:28.083 --> 00:03:29.668
I'll also need 60 gallon drums.

44
00:03:29.751 --> 00:03:31.187
Okay. Up front.
I'm gonna buy myself some

45
00:03:31.211 --> 00:03:32.963
shit since
I'm running your errand.

46
00:03:33.004 --> 00:03:34.131
Deal.

47
00:03:34.172 --> 00:03:35.507
Ooh.
Can I get a little surprise?

48
00:03:35.549 --> 00:03:37.676
No. The Amex automatically
blocks you. Jerry.

49
00:03:37.718 --> 00:03:39.344
How does it know
I'm using the card?

50
00:03:39.386 --> 00:03:40.822
Because of the kind of stuff
you buy.

51
00:03:40.846 --> 00:03:41.972
What do I buy?

52
00:03:42.013 --> 00:03:43.515
Dumb stuff. Dumb stuff.

53
00:03:44.933 --> 00:03:46.768
Computer. replace potato.

54
00:03:46.810 --> 00:03:51.273
The only Grimaldian
potato in the galaxy is here.

55
00:03:51.356 --> 00:03:52.816
God damn it!

56
00:03:54.025 --> 00:03:55.360
Let's go.

57
00:03:55.402 --> 00:03:57.112
No. thanks. You're just gonna
yell at me.

58
00:03:57.154 --> 00:03:59.090
Morty. what if I told you
I have a thing that'll make it

59
00:03:59.114 --> 00:04:01.158
so you never hear me scream
at you again?

60
00:04:01.199 --> 00:04:04.786
Wait. For real?
What kind of thing?

61
00:04:04.870 --> 00:04:06.371
Rick. what the hell?!

62
00:04:06.413 --> 00:04:09.458
Oh! Ah!

63
00:04:11.334 --> 00:04:12.627
Rick. what did you do?

64
00:04:12.711 --> 00:04:14.212
It's a Sympathid. a species

65
00:04:14.296 --> 00:04:16.173
that generates
unlimited empathy in its hosts.

66
00:04:16.214 --> 00:04:17.548
No matter what I say or do.

67
00:04:17.591 --> 00:04:19.426
the Sympathid will gloss over it

68
00:04:19.509 --> 00:04:21.094
like a Disney edit
of a slasher movie.

69
00:04:21.178 --> 00:04:22.387
Here. watch.

70
00:04:22.471 --> 00:04:23.906
You're a worthless piece
of shit. Morty!

71
00:04:23.930 --> 00:04:25.408
I'm so disappointed in you.
Rick. fuck you!

72
00:04:25.432 --> 00:04:27.058
I can still hear you screaming.

73
00:04:27.100 --> 00:04:30.312
Okay. it must need to burrow
a little bit deeper.

74
00:04:30.395 --> 00:04:31.563
There we go. Let's try again.

75
00:04:31.646 --> 00:04:34.357
You're a piece of sh...

76
00:04:34.399 --> 00:04:35.817
work. Morty!

77
00:04:35.859 --> 00:04:37.819
Like a golden retriever.
A Rick's best friend.

78
00:04:37.903 --> 00:04:39.863
And when I call you
a disappointment.

79
00:04:39.905 --> 00:04:42.574
it's because I believe you can
be so much better than you are.

80
00:04:42.616 --> 00:04:44.659
How's that? Pretty good. huh?

81
00:04:44.743 --> 00:04:46.411
It nibbles on your
empathy centers

82
00:04:46.453 --> 00:04:47.954
and poops out something
much stronger.

83
00:04:48.038 --> 00:04:50.749
Wait. It eats my empathy?
Don't worry.

84
00:04:50.791 --> 00:04:53.251
We'll only keep it in long
enough to win a potato together.

85
00:04:53.335 --> 00:04:55.420
Wait. We have to win one.
How do we...

86
00:04:55.462 --> 00:04:56.838
By dancing with the stars!

87
00:04:58.089 --> 00:04:59.090
Oh!

88
00:05:06.932 --> 00:05:07.974
Uh...

89
00:05:09.100 --> 00:05:10.435
Hey. It's okay.

90
00:05:10.519 --> 00:05:11.812
Focus on my hips.

91
00:05:11.895 --> 00:05:13.438
That's where my center
of gravity is.

92
00:05:13.480 --> 00:05:14.898
I don't know. Rick.

93
00:05:14.940 --> 00:05:16.167
You've got this.
I believe in you.

94
00:05:16.191 --> 00:05:17.859
You two are up.

95
00:05:17.943 --> 00:05:20.695
And now performing
"Claier de Lune: Epic Remix"

96
00:05:20.779 --> 00:05:23.114
King
of the Monsters" trailer.

97
00:05:23.156 --> 00:05:26.785
Rick Sanchez
and his partner Morty Smith.

98
00:05:55.897 --> 00:05:58.859
Huzzah! A triumph in movement.

99
00:05:58.942 --> 00:06:00.652
Rick. I did it! I caught you.

100
00:06:00.735 --> 00:06:02.195
I knew you could do it. buddy!

101
00:06:02.279 --> 00:06:04.531
Congratulations.
newest champions.

102
00:06:04.614 --> 00:06:06.658
Here is your reward.

103
00:06:06.741 --> 00:06:09.494
One perfect Grimaldian potato.

104
00:06:09.578 --> 00:06:11.430
And did you see
when we nailed that triple spin?

105
00:06:11.454 --> 00:06:13.832
Your timing was
metronomic. Morty.

106
00:06:13.874 --> 00:06:16.126
And then when
I caught you... oh.

107
00:06:16.751 --> 00:06:20.505
Oh. all of that
was the Sympathid. wasn't it?

108
00:06:20.547 --> 00:06:22.507
Did we actually dance or...

109
00:06:22.591 --> 00:06:24.801
The dancing was real.
The trust. the connection.

110
00:06:24.843 --> 00:06:26.678
not so much.

111
00:06:26.761 --> 00:06:28.601
It was real nice to
to feel like that with you.

112
00:06:28.638 --> 00:06:30.223
Well. it can't stay
in there forever.

113
00:06:30.307 --> 00:06:31.725
There's a bit of a comedown.

114
00:06:31.808 --> 00:06:33.351
What kind of comedown... aah!

115
00:06:35.353 --> 00:06:37.522
I feel like shit.

116
00:06:37.606 --> 00:06:39.691
Wow. it's so nice outside.

117
00:06:39.733 --> 00:06:41.151
Stop guilting me!

118
00:06:41.192 --> 00:06:43.486
Oh. my God.
This is our fifth Home Depot.

119
00:06:43.528 --> 00:06:45.447
I'm tired of depots.

120
00:06:45.530 --> 00:06:47.049
I'm not going home
without those drums.

121
00:06:47.073 --> 00:06:48.926
It's the last thing
we need on Grandpa Rick's list.

122
00:06:48.950 --> 00:06:51.286
Maybe we should
have done all the Rick shopping

123
00:06:51.369 --> 00:06:53.121
before we went Summer shopping.

124
00:06:53.163 --> 00:06:55.457
I wasn't going to miss out
on that Gucci x Kellogg's drop.

125
00:06:55.498 --> 00:06:58.251
Also. I didn't know everyone was
gonna be out of 60 gallon drums.

126
00:06:59.920 --> 00:07:01.087
What the shit?

127
00:07:01.171 --> 00:07:02.797
That dude's hoarding
all the drums!

128
00:07:02.881 --> 00:07:04.716
Why is this guy such a drum hog?

129
00:07:04.758 --> 00:07:06.760
I'm looking for the Petco.
My dog needs...

130
00:07:06.843 --> 00:07:07.844
Ah!

131
00:07:07.886 --> 00:07:09.554
Oh. he's a serial killer.

132
00:07:09.596 --> 00:07:11.389
Jesus!
We go to rescue that girl.

133
00:07:11.431 --> 00:07:12.724
We got to call the cops.

134
00:07:12.766 --> 00:07:13.784
Are you kidding?
Those drums are evidence.

135
00:07:13.808 --> 00:07:15.226
The cops will take them all.

136
00:07:15.268 --> 00:07:17.145
I need you to follow my lead.

137
00:07:21.524 --> 00:07:23.735
These hatchbacks. huh?

138
00:07:23.818 --> 00:07:25.236
Uh. is that a dead girl?

139
00:07:25.320 --> 00:07:26.905
You got me.

140
00:07:26.988 --> 00:07:28.406
Thought this rug would do
the deed.

141
00:07:28.448 --> 00:07:30.909
but it's clearly
not working out.

142
00:07:30.992 --> 00:07:34.079
Ooh. Now. those are
a good idea. Mm.

143
00:07:34.120 --> 00:07:36.081
Wish I'd thought of
60 gallon drums.

144
00:07:36.122 --> 00:07:39.668
Yeah. yeah. they're kind of
industry standard.

145
00:07:39.709 --> 00:07:43.046
Is my face red?
Amateur serial killer here.

146
00:07:43.088 --> 00:07:46.132
Uh. you think maybe
I could buy a couple off you?

147
00:07:46.216 --> 00:07:49.886
Sure.
Uh. retail price is 75 bucks.

148
00:07:49.928 --> 00:07:53.848
Oh. thanks. Saved my night.
Uh. here. I've got 100.

149
00:07:53.932 --> 00:07:55.392
Uh. I don't have any change.

150
00:07:55.433 --> 00:07:56.977
That's okay. Keep it.

151
00:07:57.060 --> 00:07:59.604
No. no. I'm a killer.
not a thief.

152
00:07:59.688 --> 00:08:04.275
Look. I've got plenty of change
at my place.

153
00:08:04.359 --> 00:08:07.529
It's right down the street.

154
00:08:07.988 --> 00:08:09.280
Oh.

155
00:08:10.782 --> 00:08:12.200
We got to save that girl.

156
00:08:12.283 --> 00:08:14.411
We got to get those drums!

157
00:08:15.578 --> 00:08:19.290
Hey. dipshit. get on the bus
so I can make fun of you!

158
00:08:19.374 --> 00:08:22.043
You've got the body
of a 14 year old boy.

159
00:08:22.127 --> 00:08:24.379
and I'm gonna beat the shit
out of that body.

160
00:08:24.421 --> 00:08:27.882
Bully is life! I'm gonna make
you so fucking sad.

161
00:08:27.924 --> 00:08:30.802
Yeah. Okay. pal.
Good luck with that.

162
00:08:32.095 --> 00:08:34.639
They're paycheck to paycheck.

163
00:08:34.681 --> 00:08:36.890
but they keep voting
against their own interests.

164
00:08:36.933 --> 00:08:39.644
I see you.
I know how much pain you're in.

165
00:08:39.727 --> 00:08:41.479
It's not your fault.

166
00:08:44.274 --> 00:08:46.526
And that's why
the Boston Tea Party

167
00:08:46.609 --> 00:08:48.570
sparked the American Revolution.

168
00:08:48.653 --> 00:08:51.364
Holy integers! A raised hand.

169
00:08:51.448 --> 00:08:52.657
This is why I only teach math.

170
00:08:52.699 --> 00:08:54.534
History classes
get you canceled.

171
00:08:54.617 --> 00:08:56.161
I just wanted to say

172
00:08:56.202 --> 00:08:58.055
that this history lesson looks
a little different

173
00:08:58.079 --> 00:09:00.165
when you empathize
with all the parties involved.

174
00:09:00.248 --> 00:09:03.251
You take a smart pill?
You're too wise for a child.

175
00:09:03.334 --> 00:09:04.669
Next time I have to sub.

176
00:09:04.753 --> 00:09:06.337
maybe you should do
the teaching.

177
00:09:06.379 --> 00:09:09.299
We should talk about the
real issue here. Mr. Goldenfold.

178
00:09:09.340 --> 00:09:11.301
Your ex-wife. Call her.

179
00:09:11.342 --> 00:09:14.345
You might not get another shot.
but you'll at least get closure.

180
00:09:14.387 --> 00:09:16.848
I wish you were my son.

181
00:09:16.890 --> 00:09:18.534
Hey. can I talk about
how I was bullied in high school

182
00:09:18.558 --> 00:09:19.851
because of my last name?

183
00:09:19.934 --> 00:09:21.162
There's time enough
for everyone.

184
00:09:21.186 --> 00:09:22.687
Principal Vagina.

185
00:09:22.937 --> 00:09:27.984
♪ Thank you. India.
thank you. Providence ♪

186
00:09:28.026 --> 00:09:32.864
♪ Thank you. disillusionment ♪

187
00:09:32.906 --> 00:09:35.825
♪ Thank you. nothingness ♪

188
00:09:35.867 --> 00:09:38.203
♪ Thank you. clarity ♪

189
00:09:38.286 --> 00:09:43.040
♪ Thank you. thank you.
silence ♪

190
00:09:43.124 --> 00:09:45.210
♪ Yeah ♪

191
00:09:46.294 --> 00:09:48.379
♪ Oh. oh ♪

192
00:09:55.553 --> 00:09:59.724
Thanks for waiting.
I had to unload the stuff.

193
00:10:00.934 --> 00:10:02.060
Tea?

194
00:10:02.102 --> 00:10:03.353
Sure.

195
00:10:03.394 --> 00:10:06.564
Uh. I don't have to be
worried about this. do I?

196
00:10:07.899 --> 00:10:10.652
I don't know. Do you?

197
00:10:14.739 --> 00:10:18.243
Let me get you that change
for the drums.

198
00:10:27.001 --> 00:10:28.294
Oh!

199
00:10:34.801 --> 00:10:37.178
Hello?
Please let me live.

200
00:10:37.262 --> 00:10:38.596
I'll do anything!

201
00:10:38.680 --> 00:10:39.973
Oh! You're alive.

202
00:10:40.056 --> 00:10:42.600
Oh. my God! Oh. my God!
Help! Help!

203
00:10:42.684 --> 00:10:44.269
Shh. shh. Okay.

204
00:10:44.352 --> 00:10:46.271
Uh. yeah.
I'm gonna get you out of there.

205
00:10:46.354 --> 00:10:47.856
Thank you. Thank you!

206
00:10:47.897 --> 00:10:50.233
If you help me get these
60 gallon drums out of here.

207
00:10:50.275 --> 00:10:51.651
Huh?

208
00:10:52.861 --> 00:10:54.154
Got to say.

209
00:10:54.237 --> 00:10:57.323
you don't seem
like a serial killer.

210
00:10:57.407 --> 00:11:01.786
Oh. I promise I'm
a nightmare person.

211
00:11:01.953 --> 00:11:03.538
The worst of the worst.

212
00:11:03.621 --> 00:11:07.375
Really? What's your signature?

213
00:11:07.458 --> 00:11:09.752
Ah. My signature.

214
00:11:09.794 --> 00:11:11.129
Uh. what's yours?

215
00:11:11.212 --> 00:11:15.091
I leave a cat toy
in my victim's pockets.

216
00:11:15.133 --> 00:11:18.469
That's why I'm the cat
and mouse killer.

217
00:11:18.553 --> 00:11:20.138
Oh.

218
00:11:20.180 --> 00:11:25.059
Well. uh. I. uh. pour
honey in the hair.

219
00:11:25.143 --> 00:11:28.646
and then I take.
a bunch of flour

220
00:11:28.688 --> 00:11:30.106
and kind of mash
it in there. too.

221
00:11:30.148 --> 00:11:32.984
and some sprinkles
and a balloon.

222
00:11:33.026 --> 00:11:36.779
and like. I make a card
that says "Happy Birthday."

223
00:11:36.821 --> 00:11:39.157
And then I wrap them
in wrapping paper.

224
00:11:39.240 --> 00:11:43.369
and that's why they call
me the Birthday Butcher.

225
00:11:43.453 --> 00:11:47.832
I kill them on their birthday
because that's a double kill.

226
00:11:47.874 --> 00:11:49.834
You know. the death of the child

227
00:11:49.918 --> 00:11:51.669
and the death of the parent.

228
00:11:51.753 --> 00:11:53.296
The parent
who metaphorically dies

229
00:11:53.338 --> 00:11:56.341
when they become a childless.
regular person again.

230
00:11:56.424 --> 00:11:58.176
It's two in one.

231
00:11:58.218 --> 00:12:02.513
And when I kill twins.
it's four at the same time.

232
00:12:02.597 --> 00:12:05.808
Oh. there's real
darkness in you.

233
00:12:08.561 --> 00:12:10.772
Hey. Rick.

234
00:12:10.813 --> 00:12:12.166
I've been thinking about
our boundaries.

235
00:12:12.190 --> 00:12:14.317
And you're right.
I shouldn't just walk in

236
00:12:14.359 --> 00:12:16.527
and expect access
to your time and attention.

237
00:12:16.611 --> 00:12:18.154
What a pleasant surprise. Morty.

238
00:12:18.196 --> 00:12:20.174
I didn't expect the Sympathid
to have lasting effects.

239
00:12:20.198 --> 00:12:22.200
Well. I'd like to
bring our trust up

240
00:12:22.283 --> 00:12:24.494
to our good old
Rick and Morty baseline.

241
00:12:24.535 --> 00:12:27.038
It's important that
you feel appreciated and seen.

242
00:12:27.121 --> 00:12:30.375
Point is. I'm gonna focus on
finding balance between my needs

243
00:12:30.416 --> 00:12:32.043
and what you want.

244
00:12:32.794 --> 00:12:34.545
Well. I want that thermometer.

245
00:12:34.587 --> 00:12:36.089
Easy!

246
00:12:36.172 --> 00:12:38.216
Do you mind if I take this?
My grandpa needs it.

247
00:12:40.385 --> 00:12:41.552
Ahh! Kaboom!

248
00:12:41.636 --> 00:12:43.221
Aw. look at the little guy!

249
00:12:43.513 --> 00:12:44.597
Morty. your arm.

250
00:12:44.681 --> 00:12:45.765
My arm?

251
00:12:45.848 --> 00:12:46.975
Yeah. buddy. Your arm.

252
00:12:47.058 --> 00:12:48.476
What's up with my arm?

253
00:12:48.559 --> 00:12:50.079
Oh. do you have
the Sympathid in right now?

254
00:12:50.103 --> 00:12:52.855
I don't know. maybe.
Is that a problem?

255
00:12:52.897 --> 00:12:54.399
How long have you had it in?

256
00:12:54.440 --> 00:12:57.360
Rick. it's making this. us.
the whole thing work.

257
